How can I update and object without selecting a record.
For example,

[ActiveRecord(Lazy=true)]
public class AdminUser
{
              ...
}

using (var sess = new Castle.ActiveRecord.SessionScope())
{
                var user = Castle.ActiveRecord.ActiveRecordMediator<Domain.AdminUser>.FindByPrimaryKey(11); //not yet select
                user.Username = "Admin"; //select from database
                System.Console.WriteLine("SET");
                System.Console.ReadLine();
                Castle.ActiveRecord.ActiveRecordMediator<Domain.BaseUser>.Save(user); //update to database
}
System.Console.WriteLine("OK");
System.Console.ReadLine();

I don't want the code to select from database everytime I set value to a property, since it effects the performance of the application, how can I write the code to just update only some property and leave those remaining untouched?
